    <a href="/2020/01/26/testing-out-a-post-with-a-youtube-video">Testing out a post with a YouTube video</a>

</h1>
<div class="entry-content"><p>Following the links on <a href="https://github.com/dommmel/jekyll-youtube">this page</a>, I added a plugin to embed a YouTube video in my posts.</p>

<p><b>Update: this plugin won’t work with GitHub, so links will have to be embedded a different way…</b></p>

<p>So let’s test it.</p>

<p>First, here’s an example of how to embed a video of the <a href="https://www.discogs.com/Lucifers-Friend-Lucifers-Friend/master/90119">Lucifer’s Friend</a> album I gave a run today:</p>

<div class="language-html highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nt">&lt;iframe</span> <span class="na">width=</span><span class="s">"560"</span> <span class="na">height=</span><span class="s">"315"</span> <span class="na">src=</span><span class="s">"https://www.youtube.com/embed/-y9AJ4HVAQg"</span> <span class="na">frameborder=</span><span class="s">"0"</span> <span class="na">allow=</span><span class="s">"accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"</span> <span class="na">allowfullscreen</span><span class="nt">&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>And if all goes well, the video should be embedded below:</p>

<iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/-y9AJ4HVAQg" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen=""></iframe>

</div>

</div>

